- Install Next.js, TypeScript, and ESLint using `npx create-next-app@latest --typescript`.
- Update ESLint configuration in `.eslintrc.json` or `.eslintrc.js`:
  ```json
  {
    "extends": [
      "next/core-web-vitals",
      "plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended",
      "prettier"
    ],
    "plugins": ["@typescript-eslint"],
    "parserOptions": {
      "ecmaVersion": 2020,
      "sourceType": "module",
      "project": "./tsconfig.json"
    },
    "rules": {
      // Custom rules here
    }
  }
  ```
- Install dependencies: `npm install --save-dev eslint @typescript-eslint/parser @typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin prettier`.
- Run ESLint with `npx eslint .` to check for linting errors.
- Configure Prettier by creating a `.prettierrc` file:
  ```json
  {
    "semi": true,
    "singleQuote": true,
    "trailingComma": "all"
  }
  ```
- Integrate ESLint with VSCode by installing the ESLint extension and configuring it to use your project's ESLint configuration.
- For Next.js 16, consider using the flat config format in `.eslintrc.json`:
  ```json
  {
    "root": true,
    "env": {
      "node": true
    },
    "parser": "@typescript-eslint/parser",
    "plugins": ["@typescript-eslint"],
    "extends": [
      "eslint:recommended",
      "plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended",
      "next/core-web-vitals"
    ],
    "rules": {
      // Custom rules here
    }
  }
  ```
- Ensure TypeScript configuration (`tsconfig.json`) is up-to-date and compatible with ESLint.
